MissionCommands.Message: Welcome to the Apollo 16 Flight Plan mission.
[Complete the TIMELINE -> Pre-Launch: Launch Preparations Checklists]
[Follow the TIMELINE -> Ascent: Boost checklist (PAGE L/2-7) ]
The Z-torquing angle will be plus 0.06. Over.
[Complete the TIMELINE -> Insertion: Post Insertion and System Checks (Item 1 - 31, PAGE L/2-11)]
[ Verify DAP 31102, 01111 ]
[ Open TLI planner and plan a TLI burn at GET ~002:33:00 (TB6 ~02:23:57) to reach a Lunar Pe of 60 nmi alt, etimated LOI at GET ~074:30:00 ]
[ Start TLI PREPARATION (PAGE L/2-27) and complete the burn. ]
[ Burn complete, proceed with the checklist. S-IVB will maneuver to sep attitude at 002:54:20. S-IVB sep planned at 003:04:20. ]
[ Complete the TIMELINE -> T&D: PRE CSM SEPARATION PREP checklist (PAGE L/3-1) ]
[ S-IVB maneuvering to sep attitude.]
[ Complete the TIMELINE -> T&D: CSM SEPARATION PREP checklist (PAGE L/3-1) ]
[ Follow the TIMELINE -> T&D: CSM SEPARATION checklist (PAGE L/3-2) to separate at 003:04:20. ]
[ Complete the checklist for TRANSPOSITION, then follow the TIMELINE -> T&D: DOCKING checklist (PAGE L/3-2) to dock before 003:14:20. ]
[ Complete the TIMELINE -> T&D: POST DOCKING checklist (PAGE L/3-4). ]
[ Complete the TIMELINE -> T&D: CM/LM PRESSURE EQUALIZATION checklist (PAGE L/3-5). ]
[ Complete the TIMELINE -> T&D: TUNNEL HATCH REMOVAL checklist (PAGE L/3-5). ]
[ Complete the TIMELINE -> T&D: LM UMBILICAL CONNECTIONS checklist (PAGE L/3-5). ]
[ Complete the TIMELINE -> T&D: HATCH INSTALLATION checklist (PAGE L/3-5). ]
[ Complete the TIMELINE -> T&D: PRE LM SEP & EJECTION checklist (PAGE L/3-5). CSM/LM EJECTION at 003:59:20 ]
[ Follow the TIMELINE -> T&D: LM SEP & EJECTION checklist (PAGE L/3-6) eject from the S-IVB at 003:59:20 ]
[ Complete the TIMELINE -> T&D: POST LM EJECTION checklist (PAGE L/3-6) ]
[ Maneuver to view S-IVB in HATCH WINDOW by 04:12:00 ]
[ S-IVB YAW MNVR ]
[ S-IVB APS EVASIVE BURN ]
[ Charge Battery B (TIMELINE -> SYSTEMS 1: EPS -> Battery Charging) ]
[ Use CREW MEMBERS -> Request REFSMMATs -> Request PTC REFSMMAT ]
[ P52, Option 3 (LAUNCH ORIENT) ]
[ P52, Option 1 (PTC ORIENT) ]
[ Complete a GDC ALIGN to align the GDC with the IMU containing the new PTC ORIENT ]
[ CSM SYSTEMS CHECK: DEACTIVATE PRIMARY EVAP (PAGE S/1-6) ]
[ P52, Option 3 (PTC ORIENT) + GDC ALIGN ]
[ No MCC-1 ]
[ Vent batteries until system test 7A = 0 ]
[ LiOH canister change: A ]
[ Maneuver to center Earth in window and photograph it ]
[ Follow the TIMELINE -> G&C 7 - PTC/ORBRATE -> (V79) ORBRATE/PTC to set up the PTC roll at 0, 270, 0 ]
[ TIMELINE -> SYSTEMS 1 - GENERAL -> PRE-SLEEP CHECKLIST (PAGE S/1-29) ]
[ Configure: H2 HEATERS 1&2 - AUTO (VERIFY); H2 FANS 3 - AUTO; O2 HEATERS 1&2 - OFF; O2 HEATERS 3 - AUTO ]
[ Wake up time: 023:00:00 ]
[ TIMELINE -> SYSTEMS 1 - GENERAL -> POST-SLEEP CHECKLIST (PAGE S/1-29) ]
[ Charge Battery A (CM AOH -> SYSTEMS: EPS -> Battery Charging) - follow the coasting and house keeping schedule as written in the Mission Details checklist from now on.]
[You have reached the Lunar Sphere of Influence]
[Plan and execute the LOI burn with a target Ap of 170 nmi and a Pe of 60 nmi]

Title: APOLLO 16 (FLIGHT PLAN)
Description: The crew of Apollo 16 is in the process of preparing the craft for ascent.
